items.Video_Title: Weekday Lunch Vlog | Paneer Kadai | Kichdi recipe | Best lunch | A Day in my life | 5am routine
items.Video_Description:
Be it veg or non-veg, preparing something special is always what I love to do for my family. And be it a complete veg meal for my non-veg eating family, my kids know mom will always try to bring out the best. The secret ingredient to any dish that’s cooked at home is love. You add a pinch of it, it tastes like never before. Be it just bread with butter, an egg sandwich, or a simple meal. Cook with love, anything can taste the best. 

Try to teach your boys a few lessons about equality in gender because mannerism needs to be from home. And it’s because our culture needs to change. Some bugs need to be fixed. And please do not burden them as well. Being parents, both are equally responsible for bringing up “Children” equally. Yes, I meant Children and not a girl or a boy. Physically and biologically there are differences that none can change. But I am talking about other stuff. Being the only girl child in the family, along with 2 siblings who are my brothers, I had all the pampering from my father. But there were a few challenges I faced. 

Again, this topic can go on and on. Let’s keep it for other vlogs right?

Hope you enjoyed this video and I’ll see you at the next

Take care, everyone,

Love you all

Soul/R&B music is a genre of popular music that originated in the United States in the late 1950s. It is characterized by a strong emphasis on vocals, often with a gospel-inspired emotional intensity, and a driving rhythm and blues beat. Soul/R&B music often deals with themes of love, loss, and social justice.

Soul/R&B music has had a profound impact on popular culture. It has been used in movies, television shows, and commercials. It has also been covered by many different artists, from jazz musicians to rock bands.
